<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="65" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[835,1472,194,345]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[835,971,194,218]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Diagnosis. –</emphasis>
The new species can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authority="Tong &amp; Li, 2007" authorityName="Tong &amp; Li" authorityYear="2007" class="Arachnida" family="Psilodercidae" genus="Flexicrurum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flexicrurum" status="new species">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">F. flexicrurum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[976,1110,226,249]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Tong &amp; Li, 2007" authorityName="Tong &amp; Li" authorityYear="2007" box="[1172,1317,227,250]" class="Arachnida" family="Psilodercidae" genus="Flexicrurum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longispina" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[1172,1317,227,250]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">F. longispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1334,1468,226,249]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, by the different patterns of ventral and dorsal abdomen, the differences of male palp details, and the shorter legs and the smaller body size.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="69" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[835,1472,386,793]" lastBlockId="6.[136,775,193,408]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="69" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[835,988,386,410]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Description. –</emphasis>
Male: Total length 1.39. Carapace 0.85 long, 0.74 wide; abdomen 0.88 long, 0.46 wide. Pattern of carapace as 
<taxonomicName authority="Tong &amp; Li, 2007" authorityName="Tong &amp; Li" authorityYear="2007" box="[865,1020,451,474]" class="Arachnida" family="Psilodercidae" genus="Flexicrurum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flexicrurum" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[865,1020,451,474]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">F. flexicrurum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1035,1168,450,473]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but without the light round patch before thoracic anterior margin that presented in 
<taxonomicName authority="Tong &amp; Li, 2007" authorityName="Tong &amp; Li" authorityYear="2007" class="Arachnida" family="Psilodercidae" genus="Flexicrurum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flexicrurum" status="new species">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">F. flexicrurum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[976,1110,514,537]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
. Clypeus as 
<taxonomicName authority="Tong &amp; Li, 2007" authorityName="Tong &amp; Li" authorityYear="2007" box="[1253,1410,515,538]" class="Arachnida" family="Psilodercidae" genus="Flexicrurum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flexicrurum" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[1253,1410,515,538]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">F. flexicrurum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="2" pageNumber="65" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, the ratio of carapace to clypeus is about 3: 1. Chelicerae creamy. Cheliceral promargin without teeth, retromargin with 2 small teeth. The posterior surface of fang provided with 13 small denticles. Maxillae light pigmented, labium dark. Sternum dark. Abdomen is nearly perpendicular to carapace in lateral view, and with complicated patterns on dorsal and ventral surfaces. Legs light brown, tibia with one white ring distally. Leg measurements: I 7.64 (2.05, 0.25, 2.28, 2.10, 0.96); II 5.71 (1.58, 0.25, 1.65, 1.53, 0.70); III 4.53 (1.31, 0.23, 1.21, 1.21, 0.57); IV 6.92 (1.93, 0.23, 2.03, 1.98, 0.75). Leg formula: 1 4 2 3. Palp measurements: 1.14 (0.50, 0.18, 0.30, 0.16), bulb 0.33 long. Palpal femur, patella and tibia modified as 
<taxonomicName authority="Tong &amp; Li, 2007" authorityName="Tong &amp; Li" authorityYear="2007" box="[366,519,321,344]" class="Arachnida" family="Psilodercidae" genus="Flexicrurum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flexicrurum" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[366,519,321,344]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">F. flexicrurum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[532,663,321,344]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
. Tibia and tarsus light pigmented. Tarsus with a strong lateral protrusion. Bulb with a slender apophysis. Conductor complicated.
</paragraph>
